## 🔒 Locking Mechanism

### Pessimistic Locking Explained

**Why Pessimistic Locking?**

Inventory operations require pessimistic locking because:
1. **High Contention:** Multiple cashiers may update same product
2. **Data Integrity:** Must prevent overselling
3. **Consistency:** Quantity must be accurate
4. **Simplicity:** Easier than optimistic locking for this use case

**How It Works:**

```
Thread 1                          Thread 2
   │                                 │
   ├─ SELECT ... FOR UPDATE          │
   │  (Acquires lock) 🔒             │
   │                                 │
   ├─ Read quantity: 100             │
   │                                 ├─ SELECT ... FOR UPDATE
   ├─ Validate: 100 >= 30 ✅         │  (Waits for lock...) ⏳
   │                                 │
   ├─ Update: 100 - 30 = 70          │
   │                                 │
   ├─ COMMIT                         │
   │  (Releases lock) 🔓             │
   │                                 │
   │                                 ├─ (Lock acquired) 🔒
   │                                 │
   │                                 ├─ Read quantity: 70
   │                                 │
   │                                 ├─ Validate: 70 >= 40 ✅
   │                                 │
   │                                 ├─ Update: 70 - 40 = 30
   │                                 │
   │                                 └─ COMMIT
   │                                    (Releases lock) 🔓
   │
   ▼                                 ▼
Final quantity: 30 ✅ (Correct!)
```

**Without Locking (Race Condition):**

```
Thread 1                          Thread 2
   │                                 │
   ├─ SELECT (no lock)               │
   │  Read quantity: 100             ├─ SELECT (no lock)
   │                                 │  Read quantity: 100
   ├─ Validate: 100 >= 30 ✅         │
   │                                 ├─ Validate: 100 >= 40 ✅
   ├─ Update: 100 - 30 = 70          │
   │                                 ├─ Update: 100 - 40 = 60
   ├─ COMMIT                         │
   │                                 └─ COMMIT
   │                                 
   ▼                                 ▼
Final quantity: 60 ❌ (Lost update! Should be 30)
```

